Applies software development expertise spanning modern front-end web development languages, technologies, and frameworks; employing sound software engineering principles. Performs complex analysis, software design using formal and informal specifications, block diagrams and logic flow charts, as well as other design techniques.  Utilizes Computer Aided Software Engineering (CASE) tools.  Develops, tests, debugs, and refines the computer software to produce the required product.  Prepares required documentation, including both program-level and user-level documentation. Enhances software to reduce operating time or improve efficiency. Experienced in software accessibility and design systems

raw_data.title: Subject Matter Expert
raw_data.description: A Subject Matter Expert is an individual whose qualifications and/or particular expertise are exceptional and/or highly unique.  They are ypically identified as recognized Industry leaders for a given area of expertise.  Subject Matter Experts typically perform the following kinds of functions:  Initiates, supervises, and/or develops requirements from a project’s inception to conclusion for complex to extremely complex programs; Provides strategic advice, technical guidance and expertise to program and project staff; Provides detailed analysis, evaluation and recommendations for improvements, optimization development, and/or maintenance efforts for client-specific or mission critical challenges/issues; Consults with client to define need or problem supervises studies and leads surveys to collect and analyze data to provide advice and recommend solutions.

raw_data.title: (Design) Researcher
raw_data.description: Responsible with all functions related to design research with a focus on improving the acceptance of the digital products delivered by the client and the customer.  Responsible for conducting research that will lead to increased understanding of end user needs, exploring the requirements necessary for the team to deliver products, and guiding the digital products through testing. They work with the product, technology, design and development team to map out the customer needs, client needs, and develop a series of activities to help the team acquire the necessary knowledge to deliver on the digital product during the discovery phase. A Design Research is also well versed in multiple capabilities within the research field and deliver research guides and studies, proofs of concept, scripts, reports, and other tools that help the team improve the digital product to be delivered.
